# Sierra Beamer Template - Cursor AI Rules

## Overview

This is a LaTeX Beamer presentation template for Sierra AI. When helping users create or edit presentations, follow these guidelines to ensure slides match Sierra's brand identity.

## Build Command

To compile presentations, run:
```bash
make build
```
Or directly:
```bash
xelatex <filename>.tex
```

## File Structure

- `*.tex` - Main presentation file(s) to edit
- `*.sty` - Theme files (DO NOT EDIT)
- `assets/` - Background images and logos
- `fonts/` - Inter font family (bundled)

## Sierra Brand Colors

Use these named colors in presentations:

### Primary (for backgrounds, emphasis)
- `SierraDarkGreen` (#05351D) - Dark backgrounds
- `SierraGreen` (#006838) - Primary brand green
- `SierraCharcoal` (#302E2D) - Titles, headings
- `SierraTaupe` (#625E5B) - Body text

### Secondary (for accents, highlights)
- `SierraOrange` (#F96205) - Alerts, emphasis
- `SierraBlue` (#8BBFF5) - Secondary accent
- `SierraGray` (#C1BCB7) - Muted elements

### Backgrounds
- `SierraBone` / `SierraBeige` (#F6F5F3) - Light slide background
- `SierraWhite` (#FFFFFF) - White

## Slide Types

### 1. Title Slide (with forest background)
```latex
{
\usebackgroundtemplate{%
  \includegraphics[width=\paperwidth,height=\paperheight]{assets/sierra-forest-bg.png}%
}
\begin{frame}[plain]
  \titlepage
\end{frame}
}
```

### 2. Section Divider (with gradient background)
```latex
{
\usebackgroundtemplate{%
  \includegraphics[width=\paperwidth,height=\paperheight]{assets/sierra-gradient-bg.png}%
}
\begin{frame}[plain]
  \centering\vfill
  {\fontsize{32}{38}\selectfont\interlight\textcolor{SierraWhite}{Section Title}}
  \vfill
\end{frame}
}
```

### 3. Basic Content Slide
```latex
\begin{frame}{Slide Title}
  Your content here.
  
  \begin{itemize}
    \item First point
    \item Second point
    \item Third point
  \end{itemize}
\end{frame}
```

### 4. Slide with Subtitle
```latex
\begin{frame}{Main Title}
  \framesubtitle{Subtitle text}
  
  Content here...
\end{frame}
```

### 5. Two-Column Layout
```latex
\begin{frame}{Two Columns}
  \begin{columns}[T]
    \begin{column}{0.48\textwidth}
      \textbf{Left Column}
      
      Left content...
    \end{column}
    \begin{column}{0.48\textwidth}
      \textbf{Right Column}
      
      Right content...
    \end{column}
  \end{columns}
\end{frame}
```

### 6. Statement Slide (Light)
```latex
{
\setbeamercolor{background canvas}{bg=SierraBone}
\begin{frame}[plain]
  \centering\vfill
  {\fontsize{24}{30}\selectfont\interlight\textcolor{SierraCharcoal}{%
    Your key statement here.%
  }}
  \vfill
\end{frame}
}
```

### 7. Statement Slide (Green)
```latex
{
\setbeamercolor{background canvas}{bg=SierraGreen}
\begin{frame}[plain]
  \centering\vfill
  {\fontsize{24}{30}\selectfont\interlight\textcolor{SierraWhite}{%
    Your impactful message.%
  }}
  \vfill
\end{frame}
}
```

### 8. Quote Slide
```latex
{
\setbeamercolor{background canvas}{bg=SierraBone}
\begin{frame}[plain]
  \centering\vfill
  \begin{minipage}{0.75\paperwidth}
    \centering
    {\fontsize{18}{24}\selectfont\interlight\textcolor{SierraCharcoal}{%
      "Your quote text here."%
    }}
    \vspace{1.5em}
    
    {\fontsize{11}{13}\selectfont\intermedium\textcolor{SierraTaupe}{Speaker Name}}
    
    {\fontsize{9}{11}\selectfont\interlight\textcolor{SierraTaupe}{Title/Role}}
  \end{minipage}
  \vfill
\end{frame}
}
```

### 9. Blocks (Info boxes)
```latex
\begin{frame}{With Blocks}
  \begin{block}{Standard Block}
    Green header, white body - for general information
  \end{block}
  
  \begin{alertblock}{Alert Block}
    Orange header - for warnings or important points
  \end{alertblock}
  
  \begin{exampleblock}{Example Block}
    Blue/teal header - for examples
  \end{exampleblock}
\end{frame}
```

### 10. Table
```latex
\begin{frame}{Data Table}
  \begin{table}
    \centering
    \begin{tabular}{lcc}
      \toprule
      \textbf{Item} & \textbf{Value 1} & \textbf{Value 2} \\
      \midrule
      Row 1 & 100 & 200 \\
      Row 2 & 150 & 250 \\
      \bottomrule
    \end{tabular}
    \caption{Table caption}
  \end{table}
\end{frame}
```

### 11. Thank You Slide
```latex
{
\usebackgroundtemplate{%
  \includegraphics[width=\paperwidth,height=\paperheight]{assets/sierra-dusk-bg.jpg}%
}
\begin{frame}[plain]
  \centering\vfill
  {\fontsize{48}{58}\selectfont\interlight\textcolor{SierraWhite}{Thank you{\large\textbullet}}}
  \vspace{2.5em}
  \includegraphics[height=1.5cm]{assets/sierra-logo-white.png}
  \vfill
\end{frame}
}
```

## Typography Commands

- `\interlight` - Light weight (titles, statements)
- `\interregular` - Regular weight (body text)
- `\intermedium` - Medium weight (subtitles)
- `\intersemibold` - SemiBold weight (headings)
- `\interbold` - Bold weight (strong emphasis)

## Best Practices

1. **Keep slides simple** - Limit to 3-5 bullet points per slide
2. **Use consistent colors** - Stick to Sierra brand palette
3. **One idea per slide** - Break complex topics into multiple slides
4. **Use statement slides** - For key takeaways and transitions
5. **Section dividers** - Help audience follow the structure

## Common User Requests

When users ask to:
- "Add a slide about X" → Create a basic content slide with title and bullet points
- "Create a comparison" → Use two-column layout
- "Add a quote" → Use quote slide format
- "Make an impact" → Use statement slide (green for emphasis)
- "Add a section" → Use section divider with gradient background
- "Add a table" → Use booktabs style table

## Important Notes

- Always maintain the slide structure with `\begin{frame}` and `\end{frame}`
- Use `[plain]` option for full-screen slides (title, statement, thank you)
- Background images must be wrapped in `{ }` braces for scoping
- The theme automatically handles colors, fonts, and spacing


